message_1:
What is the cross-section for a neutron-induced fission reaction in a uranium-235 nucleus at an incident energy of 1 MeV? Given that the target nucleus is initially in its ground state and that the fission cross-section is approximately constant in this energy range. Use the formula: 

cross-section = \frac{reaction\ rate}{flux}

where the reaction rate is the number of reactions per unit time and per unit volume, and the flux is the number of incident particles per unit area per unit time.
